16. How does Git integrate with Jenkins?

Answer:

Developer pushes code to Git.
A webhook notifies Jenkins.
Jenkins checks out the latest code.
Jenkins builds the application.
Runs automated tests.
Creates artifacts or Docker images.
Deploys to staging or production.
17. Difference between git reset and git revert
git reset	git revert
Removes commits from history	Creates a new commit to undo changes
Rewrites history	Preserves history
Risky on shared branches	Safe for shared branches
18. How do you check commit history?
git log

Compact format:

git log --oneline

Graph view:

git log --graph --oneline --all
19. What is the purpose of git fetch?

Answer:
It downloads changes from the remote repository without merging them into your current branch, allowing you to review updates before integrating them.

20. How do you resolve conflicts in a Pull Request?

Answer:

Fetch the latest changes.
Merge or rebase the target branch into your feature branch.
Resolve conflicts locally.
Test the application.
Commit the resolution.
Push the updated branch.
Verify the Pull Request is conflict-free.
